name: Pub Crawl
description: We're getting on it tonight! We'll start at Brewdog, before moving onto The Eagle, and finishing at The White Rabbit.

schedule.description: We'll kick things off here with craft beer and an amazing atmosphere.

address_components.short_name: The City of Brighton and Hove

result.name: BrewDog Brighton

reviews.text:
This place is awesome! I will say, on a uni budget the drinks are kind of pricey, but if you're a beer lover it's so worth it. The bartenders are so knowledgeable on what they have to offer. Even if you have no idea whatsoever what you're interested in, they'll help you get there and let you sample whatever you'd like. The food is also delicious! 

SN: They even have cute art messages in the bathroom :)
Tasty burgers and excellent selection of beer. Reasonable price for Brighton. Definitely recommend.
Lovely food. Nice atmosphere and staff very polite and helpful. Not an ale drinker, but I loved this place.
Great beer-tasting experience and yummy nibbles. If you like BrewDog beers you should go to one of their bars and see what they're all about.

It's a craft beer pub, so brace yourself for pretension. The bloke who served us sounded like Jilly Goolden at times, but he was very friendly and the beer was delicious. I had a (rather rudely named) Dutch Udder. The prices are not always for a pint, so check what you are getting as they serve thirds.

reviews.text: Excellent Sunday roast dinner. We booked a table for seven, which was fortunate because 30 mins after we arrived the place was crammed. Shows how popular it is. Two young children were well catered for. Portions were good and prices were very reasonable
An excellent meal, really tasty home made beef burger.  Very good.
Best pub Sunday lunch ive had. Delicious fresh and good quality meat.  All with a home cooked taste. I'd visit Brighton just doe their food.
Friendly bar staff and a decent enough burger. Not amazing but still good
Great food, great service (no coffee)

schedule.description: For those who can stick it out, we'll finish the night here.

result.name: The White Rabbit

reviews.text:
Great place to people watch on a nice day. Just beware of a constant stream of homeless/smackheads pestering you for money (You can't do much as it's the street) but it's CONSTANT. The pub itself used to be a great place, not sure but its changed a fair deal in the years I've been going.

Certain staff are friendly and really nice, a few are just annoyed too be there it seems. The food is really nice tho, bit expensive but tasty.

Just arrived in time for the last song from the Sunday night open mic event. I'm blown away with the easygoing bar staff dealing with punters dancing on the tables. Yep great vibe, great music and great punters. And all on a Sunday evening... God Bess The Whit Rabbit.... I'll deff be back!

Super baby friendly pub in the heart of the North Laines. They were so accommodating, I breastfed my tiny baby and ordered a small drink and my Mum ordered a glass of wine. They were lovely and kind and just utterly delightful a. D brought us some chips while we sat in comfy seating. Can't recommend then enough.
great atmosphere and nice staff. looks just the way a pub should be. well worth a visit
Good pub with a decent burger, but if you actually want to talk to the person you're with, you have to shout over the super-loud music.

reviews.text: Not a bad pub. Lots of tables and not too expensive for Brighton. The main let-down is the quite unbelievably bad bar service. Went on Nov 4th 2017 and it was like the staff were deliberately trying to create a queue. There were several people behind the bar faffing and idling and avoiding eye contact. Even the vaguest suggestion of urgency from any one of the too-cool-to-do-my-job hipsters would have made the whole experience much more palatable but I left feeling just a little bit cross.

Nice pub, pop up cinema with nice staff who couldn’t have been apologetic about their appalling food! Hope they sort their new chef out - teething problems is putting it mildly. It will be a loooooong time before I’d risk ordering their food again.
Excellent pub, really good range of beers and a really good food menu. Loads of things going on here too. Only negative would be not a great outside space to drink.

Some of the worst food I've ever been exposed to. They manage to impress you through 3 courses by somehow being consistently more dissapointing than what you were last forced to eat. 

Run.

Large unpretentious brew house with cool events and food specials like bottomless brunch and bottomless Sunday roast.

Floor and tables do have a tendency to get sticky and because of the size of the place it attracts stags and hens. 

Great for big groups and watching the World Cup. It's a bit pricy and it can get real noisy when it's full

reviews.text: Really nice atmosphere and dancing. Lots of lovely dressed people and great live music. Have seen wedding parties here,though it's not a super fancy establishment. It's really quirky with lots of character but the drinks are a little on the expensive side. Always a good night had here. Toilets are a bit grotty .

We chose this place as it offered an exotic cuisine which is unusual in uk - East African/Indian fusion food. Decent ambience. Good service. 
But the chef has no soul.  
All the dishes were cooked well but the chef has no clue about masalas & taste in general. 
We were quite excited on entering. Left very disappointed.

Was here last night and we had a great time. Loved the old school funky 70s and soul music 🎶 good atmosphere, met some lovely people in the smoking area. Definitely come back when we visit Brighton again ❤️
Came for drinks. Had a sunday lunch. The lamb shank was incredible. The food was delicious and the staff are bloody lovely. Love this pub!

Wouldn't let us in because we were apparently part of a group that had been there previously In the night, we most definitely had not been there previously in the night, as my partner and I were out for a meal for my birthday, which was just the two of us! We asked a few questions about why they wouldn't let us in but they completely and rudely dismissed us!! Considering they were recommended our first experience has been terrible and I would not recommend this establishment myself, to be perfectly honest I'll tell everyone I know to avoid it at all costs!!

result.name: Brighton Beach

reviews.text:
All the fun of the seaside. This very
popular space has been entertaining 
families for generations. Lots going on.
Plenty of places for food, drinks and
ice-cream. Fantastic play areas for kids.
Unfortunately this beach is all pebbles 
and not sand. Only when the tide is out 
can the buckets and spades get to work.

Like thousands of other people, we go to Brighton beach because it's easy to get there from London. It's not the greatest beach around; piles of stones making it hard to walk, a greyish sea, and aggressive seagulls are a few of the highlights you find there. At least there's plenty of decent places to eat and drink along the prom, and the beach is pretty well looked after by the Council. They also have RNLI life guards on duty too, which makes it a safe place for a swim if you fancy it. Overall there's plenty of better beaches, but it's hard to beat it for the convenience.
It's Brighton beach. Pebbles. Sand when the tide is out. Well maintained and washed daily by rain and sea..
It's not for fun to go there playing games anything you want really
Beautiful sunsets by the old pier
